Well, I just recently began charm-soloing with my 23 enchanter in LOIO and I am <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> loving it</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->!  I see some Necro standing on the beach going: <br>
&quot;/pet attack&quot; &quot;/pet back off&quot; /pet sit down&quot; &quot;Lich&quot;, lather rinse repeat, lather rinse repeat.  <br>
While meanwhile I'm: &quot;Tashan, charm!  Tashan, root!  /pet attack!  Slow!  Root!  Color Flux!  Charm!  /pet attack!  /pet guard here!  Invis, Tashan, charm!  Root!&quot; <br>
Dodging and weaving and running circles and bending the surroundings to my will, muaha.  <br>
I know I'm still young at the point where I can tank for a couple rounds if the situation gets dire, and that in a few short levels the MOBs will simply hit to hard for that to be an option anymore.  Still I think its good to learn these soloing basics early on.  Here's what I did to prime myself:<br>
<br>
A) I got myself something nice and low blue, a MOB that wouldn't really pose a threat if he slipped my harness but enough to keep me on my toes.<br>
<br>
B) I took my new pet to some green MOBs and had him beat the snot out of them.  During one of these fights a weak little green goblin jumped me and I had some very cool practice juggling mez, root, and re-charm.<br>
<br>
C) Eventually I moved on to bigger MOBs and started practicing &quot;Pet swapping&quot;.  Where my original pet is low on health, so I tell him to &quot;stay&quot; and run far off to find a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> better</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pet.  When I find a new gobby or sarnak I invis up and charm the full-health one, who proceeds to beat on my former buddy (TWO can play at the traitor game!).  I did this very successfully tonight.  The chain finally ended when my pet killed the MOB and had very low HP left.  His charm broke and he started to slowly walk away.  One happy nuke later and he dropped like a stone, and I was one blue bub richer.<br>
<br>
Obviously as time and levels grow my fail-safe memblur will whither away into uselessness but even then I feel I can still enjoy this tactic.  I just love having people say &quot;Are you crazy?  Charm is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> suicide</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->!&quot; and then having my exp. bar shoot up another notch.  I can't wait till I hit those Velious Giants and try this out on 'em.<br>
<br>
The Enchanter class is just amazing, I love the idea of manipulating everything to do my bidding!  <br>
/pet move my experience bar!<br>
<br>
Again, thanks for posting this!<br>
